text:
Just an interesting bit of trivia from MaRo:
 
“The Vedalken were first created as replacement for Merfolk when they were removed from the game (they obviously came back). They were designed as a race that more embodied the ideals of blue. And they had four arms from the beginning.”
Not to beat a dead horse but I'm genuinely shocked that Wotc struggles so much with this FNM promo thing

There's a ton of inexpensive yet popular cards they could easily make promos people will seek out while simultaneously not cutting into their desire to keep the really good stuff as chase product for masters sets. Obviously we're not gonna get Cabal Coffers or Lightning Greaves again, and I'm fine with that.

But Ghost Quarter is a 2 dollar card that is pretty heavily played in two formats. Print up a cool new art foil Ghost Quarter and the EDH and Modern players I know will want one. Mystic Remora is big in EDH and pauper and doesn't have an oracle text or foil or modern border version. It's not like that is gonna be a chase card in Masters 26 or something, so make it an FNM promo.
Seems like a good chance to bring back full art cards or textless promos too. A full art Abrade would get standard and modern players to the house. A textless Dark Ritual or Counterspell.
Seriously, I could come up with ten years worth of promos in an hour that are popular across multiple formats while not cutting into stuff they want to as chase cards in reprint sets

No argument there...I'm not sure what the struggle is, but it must be some kind of inside baseball or political element. Perhaps there's more tension than we realize between the various project groups about claiming reprints and FNM promos always draw the short-end of the stick.
In talking about Standard-legal promos, Stoddard/Forsythe whoever said they’re hopefully now able to roll back their timeline to decide on FNM promos so they can actually pick good ones.
And the testing design group should be able to help more with that
Locking into standard-legal promos seems like such a silly, arbitrary limitation. They're setting themselves up to fail
They've said they won't do text less again and that makes me sad.
Given they're for FNM and most of FNM is Standard, there's certainly logic to it.
It's pretty tenuous logic though

I mean, even if they pick "good"ones I'm still not sure that brings people to the shop besides the ones already showing up. Then again according to Maro there wasn't a rise in attendence for Path to Exile either even though FNM where I played was radically larger.
Fnm for Edh! That’ll draw in more people!
